  "name": "Morrison CFD Hemolysis Credibility Assessment — FDA Generic Centrifugal Blood Pump (CPB)",
  "description": "Credibility assessment under ASME V&V 40-2018 for a CFD model predicting hemolysis in the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump operated under cardiopulmonary bypass conditions. The model is intended to identify worst-case hemolysis operating points for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Thirteen credibility factors are evaluated: seven assessed (all meeting required levels) and six not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The submission targets regulatory acceptance for pre-market submission to the FDA.",
